DTSTART:20260411T140000Z
DTEND:20260411T153000Z
SUMMARY:Walking Tour: Downtown Tampa
LOCATION:400 N. Franklin St. Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Looking for a unique activity to do in Tampa Bay? Join the Tam
 pa Bay History Center for an immersive downtown walking tour. This guided 
 trek leads you past some of the citys most storied landmarks\, including C
 ity Hall\, Sacred Heart Church\, the Floridan Palace Hotel\, and The Hub\,
  Tampas oldest bar. Along the route\, your guide will share the stories th
 at connect these sites to the citys vibrant past. The tour lasts 90 minute
 s\, begins at 10 a.m.\, and is limited to 25 guests for a more personal ex
 perience. The route covers about one mile along sidewalks and brick street
 s\, so comfortable shoes and outdoor attire are recommended. Your starting
  point is Lykes Gaslight Park at 400 N. Franklin St.\, right in the center
  of downtown. Street parking is available nearby\, making it easy to begin
  your journey. Advance tickets are required\, and private tours can be boo
 ked by calling (813) 228-0097. Group size is small and tickets go fast. Re
 serve your spot today and experience downtown Tampa through the lens of hi
 story. Looking for other tours? Visit our walking tour page . \n\nPermalin
 k: https://www.tampa.gov/node/185851
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/185851
END:VEVENT
